byline.contributor: Palko Karasz contributed reporting from London.

abstract: Austrian authorities rescue three Syrian children from smugglers' small van crammed with 23 others migrants near Braunau by German border; driver is arrested and children are being treated for severe dehydration at Braunau hospital.
lead_paragraph: The authorities said the 5- and 6-year-olds were treated for dehydration after the vehicle they were traveling in was seized after a chase.

headline.main: 3 Children Among Migrants Found Crammed in Van Are Hospitalized in Austria
headline.print_headline: 3 Children Among Migrants Crammed Into Bus Are Hospitalized in Austria
